# Falling Game - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a Next.js mobile game project with TypeScript, focusing on falling apple mechanics. The project uses a 480px mobile container and optimizes for game performance.

## Key Rules
- Always use MobileContainer wrapper
- Never exceed 480px width
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Optimize for 60fps performance
- Follow mobile-first design

## File References
- Main container: src/components/MobileLayoutContainer.tsx
- Window size hook: src/utils/useInnerSize.tsx
- Next.js config: next.config.ts
- TypeScript config: tsconfig.json

## Development Patterns
- Use inline styles for dynamic elements
- Implement proper touch event handling
- Follow naming conventions strictly
- Optimize assets and performance

## Game Development
- Use absolute positioning for game elements
- Implement collision detection
- Use requestAnimationFrame for game loops
- Monitor frame rate and memory usage

## Mobile Optimization
- Respect 480px container constraint
- Use touch-friendly button sizes (44px min)
- Implement proper touch event handling
- Optimize for battery life 